This git repositories is meant to store the input and output file
It can be usefull for post processign as well. to do so the process is:
1. use hpc to obtain the output file to postprocess (o* or ndb*)
2. git add, commit and push to the remote (.gitignore will select only o and in file so for ndb.file we must force the add with git add -f [ndb.*]
3. to avoid to pull everything in the local laptop we sparse the checkout  before pulling:
	git sparse-checkout [dir to show and download in local] and select the dir containing the file we want to postprocess
4. git pull origin master to pull the update from origin repo to master branch in local 
(nb. since we parsed the checkout only the directory selected at point 3 will be visible; to show another directory rerun git sparse-checkout [another dir])
5. use postprocessign tools
6. git add the pdf file or any other postproc output file
7. git commit -m ""
8. git push origin master to pust the new postporoc pdf files to the repo. 

